This paper deals with analyzing and detecting different types of harassment in online content, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis and classification, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with ethical and societal issues related to online harassment, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
